== s3toad ==

A quick and ugly utility for working with AWS S3.

== Build ==

mvn clean install assembly:single

== Usage ==

<pre>
$ java -jar s3toad-0.0.2-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar args
</pre>
run it with no args to get usage help.

If it is run on a ec2 instance then it will auto detect the roles of the instance, otherwise it can be configured via env-vars. e.g.:
<pre>
$ export AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID="my-id-key" export AWS_SECRET_KEY="my-secret-key"
</pre>

To upload:
<pre>
$ java -jar s3toad-0.0.2-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar push ~/media/file some-bucket 5
</pre>
where 5 is number of threads to use when uploading.

To generate pre-auth URLs (valid for 1 hour):
<pre>
$ java -jar s3toad-0.0.2-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar url some-bucket /my-file.tar.gz
</pre>
Then give the URL it returns to curl, wget, axel or some other download tool.

To get partial-upload stats:
<pre>
$ java -jar s3toad-0.0.2-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar status some-bucket
</pre>

To clean up all incomplete multi-part uploads:
<pre>
$ java -jar s3toad-0.0.2-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar clean some-bucket
</pre>
